EU Wants Bank Bondholders to Take Bigger Crisis Losses, FTD Says

-- B y   J e f f   B l a c k
-- 
2011-12-01T08:55:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-01/eu-wants-bank-bondholders-to-take-bigger-crisis-losses-ftd-says.html
The European Union wants creditors
and shareholders of European banks to take bigger losses in the
event that a financial institution is restructured or wound up,
 Financial Times Deutschland  reported, citing draft legislation.  The draft, prepared by EU financial services commissioner
 Michel Barnier , would require senior bondholders to take losses
in event of insolvency, the newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jeff Black in Frankfurt at 
 jblack25@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
